l%20force%2C%20that%20forecast%20could%20be%20higher%20at%20around%203.5%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2230ef07e0-580f-4b35-8244-977986551b29%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ELayers%20of%20inflation%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20now%2C%20Trump's%20seemingly%20pro-growth%20policies%20mean%20optimism%2C%20especially%20among%20smaller%20domestic%20companies%20that%20would%20benefit%20most.%20The%20outcome%20could%20result%20in%20increased%20hiring%20and%20an%20uptick%20in%20labor%20demand.%20It's%20good%20news%20for%20those%20looking%20for%20a%20job%2C%20but%20it%20also%20comes%20at%20a%20time%20when%20immigration%20restrictions%20are%20expected%20to%20tighten%20labor%20supply%20further.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDecember's%20already%20strong%20labor%20readings%20suggest%20there's%20not%20much%20wiggle%20room%20before%20upsetting%20the%20balance%20of%20supply%20and%20demand.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdecember-jobs-report-unemployment-rate-employment-federal-reserve-interest-rates-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunemployment%20rate%3C%2Fa%3E%20ticked%20down%20to%204.1%25%20from%204.2%25%20the%20previous%20month%2C%20while%20256%2C000%20jobs%20were%20added.%20The%20combination%20could%20cause%20even%20further%20upward%20pressure%20on%20wage%20growth%2C%20Barraud%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20shorter%20term%2C%20Barraud%20points%20to%20a%20few%20transitory%20factors%20that%20may%20give%20CPI%20an%20additional%20bump%20up.%20They%20include%20the%20California%20wildfires%20and%20hurricanes%20that%20could%20increase%20rebuilding%20costs%20and%20homeowners%20and%20auto%20insurance%20premiums.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20there%20are%20tariffs%2C%20which%20add%20a%20layer%20of%20complication.%20Consumers%20are%20likely%20to%20pick%20up%20the%20bill%20on%20imports%20as%20a%20form%20of%20consumption%20tax.%20Goldman%20Sachs%20forecasts%20tariffs%20will%20lead%20to%20a%20one-time%200.3%25%20boost%20to%20inflation%2C%20a%20number%20that's%20not%20enough%20to%20take%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-market-interest-rate-cuts-december-jobs-report-investing-strategy-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erate%20cuts%20off%20the%20table%3C%2Fa%3E%20but%20could%20spook%20FOMC%20participants%20from%20making%20them.%20Economic%20uncertainty%20combined%20with%20a%20desire%20to%20avoid%20taking%20the%20blame%20for%20inflation's%20return%20may%20cause%20the%20central%20bank%20to%20refrain%20from%20further%20cuts%20in%20a%20wait-and-see%20approach%2C%20said%20Goldman%20Chief%20Economist%20Jan%20Hatzius%20in%20a%20recent%20note.%20The%20investment%20bank%20maintains%20expectations%20of%20two%2025-basis-point%20cuts%20in%20June%20and%20December.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Barraud%20believes%20rate%20cuts%20could%20be%20off%20the%20table%20entirely%20this%20year%20mainly%20because%20domestic%20growth%20is%20strong%20and%20will%20likely%20stay%20that%20way.%20His%20forecast%20for%20US%20GDP%202025%20is%202.3%25%2C%20above%20the%20consensus%20of%202.2%25.%20While%20he%20is%20inclined%20to%20increase%20it%2C%20he's%20waiting%20for%20further%20details%20about%20Washington's%20policy%20changes%20and%20whether%20consumer%20spending%20remains%20robust.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChan%20says%20further%20economic%20growth%20is%20also%20showing%20on%20the%20manufacturing%20front.%20December's%20new%20orders%20for%20the%20Purchasing%20Managers'%20Index%20rose%20into%20positive%20territory%20for%20the%20second%20month%20at%2052.5%25%2C%20an%20early%20indicator%20that%20the%20overall%20PMI%2C%20which%20sat%20at%2049.3%25%2C%20could%20rise%20above%2050%2C%20the%20threshold%20for%20expansion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20areas%2C%20like%20consumer%20spending%20and%20household%20net%20worth%2C%20are%20also%20up%2C%20suggesting%20that%20the%20consumer%20is%20in%20pretty%20good%20shape%2C%20which%20supports%20stickier%20inflation%2C%20Chan%20said.%20Finally%2C%20rents%20remain%20high%20as%20more%20would-be%20homeowners%20turn%20to%20short-term%20solutions%20amid%20elevated%20mortgage%20rates%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBelow%20is%20a%20chart%20from%20Morningstar%20that%20reflects%20projected%20personal%20consumption%20expenditures%20(PCE)%2C%20a%20measure%20of%20household%20spending%20on%20goods%20and%20services.%20It%20shows%20expectations%20of%20housing%20costs%20sharply%20dropping%20along%20with%20food%20and%20energy%20costs.%20Morningstar%20projects%20an%20average%20inflation%20rate%20of%201.9%25%20over%202025-28%2C%20adding%200.2%25%20for%20the%20impact%20of%20additional%20tariffs%2C%20noting%20that%20full%20implementation%20of%20tariffs%20would%20result%20in%20another%20increase%20of%201%25-2%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221116%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22CHart%20on%20PCE%20inflation%20forecast%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67993bb0eb4be2fff9a2a521%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221066%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EMorningstar%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2250cded74-c462-40c9-93e7-08baa88d12d1%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20to%20invest%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EInvestors%20looking%20for%20some%20balance%20and%20safety%20should%20consider%20%3Cstrong%3Eindustrials%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20%3Cstrong%3Ematerials%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20and%20%3Cstrong%3Eenergy%20stocks%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20all%20of%20which%20should%20hold%20up%20if%20inflation%20returns%2C%20Chan%20said.%20In%202022%2C%20these%20sectors%20outperformed%20the%20broad%20market%20amid%20the%20inflation%20spike%2C%20he%20added.%20Exchange-traded%20funds%20that%20track%20these%20sectors%20include%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fetfs%2Fvanguard-industrials-index-fund-etf-shares-us92204a6038%3FmiRedirects%3D1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVanguard%20Industrials%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fetfs%2Fthe-materials-s