ance%20management.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20some%20employers%20are%20engaging%20in%20so-called%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstealth-firing-save-costs-short-term-risk-long-term-backlash-2024-12%3Futm_source%3Dtwitter%26utm_medium%3Dsocial%26utm_campaign%3Dbusiness-sf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estealth%20firing%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20just%20in%20the%20corporate%20world.%20Last%20week%2C%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20ordered%20an%20end%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-orders-federal-dei-roles-terminated-staff-on-leave-immediately-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efederal%20DEI%20programs%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He%20also%20said%20many%20federal%20workers%20would%20need%20to%20be%20back%20in%20the%20office%20five%20days%20a%20week%20%E2%80%94%20upending%20years%20of%20WFH%20arrangements%20for%20the%20roughly%20half%20of%20employees%20who%20could%20work%20remotely%20at%20least%20part%20of%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20an%20absolutely%20terrible%20idea%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20federal%20contractor%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20told%20BI%2C%20who%20asked%20not%20to%20be%20named%20so%20she%20could%20speak%20freely%20without%20fear%20of%20repercussions.%20BI%20has%20confirmed%20her%20identity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20autonomy%20she's%20had%20meant%20she%20was%20willing%20to%20give%20more%20in%20exchange%20for%20the%20privilege%20of%20working%20from%20home%20some%20of%20the%20time.%20Rather%20than%20closing%20her%20laptop%20%26quot%3Bat%205%3A01%20p.m.%2C%26quot%3B%20if%20her%20boss%20asked%20her%20to%20take%20an%20after-hours%20meeting%2C%20she%20would%20agree.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20she%20said%2C%20she's%20considering%20looking%20for%20a%20job%20that%20allows%20for%20a%20more%20flexible%20setup%2C%20at%20least%20on%20some%20days%2C%20even%20if%20it%20meant%20earning%20less.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhite%20House%20Deputy%20Press