hitects%20I've%20talked%20to%20generally%20agree%20that%20chance%20played%20a%20big%20role%20in%20deciding%20which%20structures%20survived.%20But%20as%20Sean%20Jursnick%2C%20a%20Denver-area%20architect%2C%20puts%20it%2C%20the%20owners%20of%20the%20spared%20houses%20may%20have%20%26quot%3Bcreated%20some%20of%20their%20own%20luck.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeasures%20to%20reduce%20the%20risk%20of%20fire%20damage%20include%20straightforward%20design%20tweaks%20such%20as%20streamlining%20exteriors%20to%20eliminate%20the%20nooks%20and%20crannies%20where%20stray%20embers%20can%20settle%2C%20or%20getting%20rid%20of%20vegetation%20that%20could%20shuttle%20flames%20to%20the%20main%20structure.%20Then%20there%20are%20the%20cutting-edge%20materials%20%E2%80%94%20wrapped%20in%20jargon%20like%20%26quot%3Bcementitious%20fiber-reinforced%20composite%20building%20system%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20that%20offer%20alternatives%20to%20the%20flammable%20lumber%20that%20dominates%20home%20construction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInterventions%20by%20both%20homeowners%20and%20builders%20are%20growing%20more%20necessary%20as%20the%20risk%20of%20fires%20increases%20%E2%80%94%20and%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhomeowners-abandoned-by-private-insurance-turning-to-government-plans-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einsurers%20get%20pickier%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20which%20properties%20they'll%20cover.%20Soon%2C%20many%20people%20across%20the%20US%20may%20have%20no%20choice%20but%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgavin-newsom-reimagining-los-angeles-post-wildfire-marshall-plan-rebuild-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebuild%20smarter%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EScott%20Long%20has%20spent%20decades%20in%20pursuit%20of%20a%20material%20capable%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flumber-wood-prices-americas-economic-future-real-estate-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunseating%20lumber%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20the%20go-to%20option%20for%20home%20frames.%20The%20basics%20of%20home%20construction%20haven't%20substantially%20evolved%20since%20the%201800s%2C%20when%20building%20the%20skeletal%20structure%20out%20of%20dimensional%20lumber%20%E2%80%94%20your%20classic%20two-by-fours%2C%20etc.%20%E2%80%94%20came%20into%20fashion.%20Wood%20components%2C%20Long%20says%2C%20are%20%26quot%3Bliterally%20the%20worst%20possible%20product%20you%20could%20use%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20event%20of%20high%20winds%2C%20flooding%2C%20or%20fire%20since%20they%20burn%20(unlike%20concrete)%20and%20aren't%20as%20sturdy%20as%2C%20say%2C%20steel.%20Masking%20wood%20with%20something%20like%20magnesium%20oxide%20board%20or%20stucco%20siding%2C%20both%20of%20which%20are%20more%20resistant%20to%20fire%2C%20is%20fine%2C%20Long%20says%2C%20but%20%26quot%3Bnot%20a%20solution.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20time%20for%20change%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20Long%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BWe%20can't%20keep%20building%20the%20way%20we've%20been%20building%20up%20against%20these%20types%20of%20historic%20events.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20these%20problems%2C%20Long%20founded%20NileBuilt%20in%202019%2C%20building%20homes%20primarily%20out%20of%20fiber-reinforced%20concrete%20panels%20with%20foam%20insulation%20in%20the%20middle.%20The%20company's%20model%20homes%20look%20simple%20and%20modern%2C%20all%20flat%20roofs%20and%20sharp%20edges%2C%20and%20it%20says%20the%20materials%20can%20withstand%20temperatures%20of%20more%20than%202%2C000%20degrees%20Fahrenheit%20%E2%80%94%20the%20panels%2C%20unlike%20the%20walls%20of%20traditional%20homes%2C%20won't%20combust%20from%20the%20extreme%20heat%20of%20a%20neighboring%20fire.%20Long%20says%20the%20cost%20of%20building%20his%20homes%20roughly%20matches%20that%20of%20wood-frame%20houses.%20A%20quiet%20start%20to%202025%20for%20his%20company%20has%20turned%20into%20a%20frenzy%3B%20he%20says%20that%20even%20before%20the%20fires%2C%20the%20waitlist%20for%20one%20of%20the%20homes%20was%20just%20under%203%2C000%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEliason%20isn't%20calling%20for%20the%20kind%20of%20paradigm%20shift%20in%20building%20materials%20that%20Long%20suggests.%20He%20pointed%20to%20a%20widely%20seen%20X%20post%20showing%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FChasenGreg%2Fstatus%2F1877478755091767732%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPacific%20Palisades%20home%20that%20survived%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20little%20apparent%20damage%2C%20saying%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Bnot%20a%20concrete%20house%20or%20brick%20house%20or%20anything%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20other%20measures%20its%20owner%20took%20may%20have%20mattered%20a%20lot%20more.%20And%20wood%20has%20its%20own%20advantages%3A%20It's%20cheap%2C%20and%20lumber%20production%20doesn't%20release%20nearly%20as%20much%20carbon%20as%20concrete%20or%20steel.%20In%20the%20event%20of%20an%20earthquake%2C%20its%20pliability%20is%20a%20huge%20plus.%20For%20all%20these%20reasons%2C%20Eliason%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Bgoing%20away%20from%20wood-frame%20construction%20seems%20really%20shortsighted.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fplatform.twitter.com%2Fwidgets.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22twitter%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ENo%20words%20really%20-%20just%20a%20horror%20show.%20Some%20of%20the%20design%20choices%20we%20made%20here%20helped.%20But%20we%20were%20also%20very%20lucky.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FkpqfiRj49M%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FkpqfiRj49M%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%E2%80%94%20g%20chasen%20(%40ChasenGreg)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FChasenGreg%2Fstatus%2F1877478755091767732%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EJanuary%209%2C%202025%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20he%20advocates%20more-modest%20tweaks%20that%20can%20add%20up%20to%20real%20risk%20mitigation.%20A%20streamlined%2C%20boxy%20structure%20offers%20fewer%20places%20for%20stray%20embers%20to%20linger.%20These%20embers%20are%20often%20good%20fuel%20for%20a%20wildfire's%20spread%20%E2%80%94%20they%20can%20travel%20several%20miles%20by%20air%2C%20then%20enter%20through%20vents%20or%20settle%20on%20a%20combustible%20part%20of%20the%20home%2C%20igniting%20another%20conflagration.%20By%20getting%20rid%20of%20nooks%20and%20crannies%20like%20roof%20overhangs%20(also%20known%20as%20eaves)%20or%20little%20windows%20that%20jut%20out%20of%20the%20roof%2C%20builders%20can%20reduce%20fire%20risk.%20Materials%20also%20matter%3A%20Builders%20can%20wrap%20a%20home%20in%20noncombustible%20mineral%20wool%20and%20install%20drywall%20capable%20of%20withstanding%20an%20hour%20of%20direct%20contact%20with%20flames.%20Metal%20roofs%20are%20preferable%20to%20classic%20shingles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20house%20Eliason%20referred%20to%20has%20many%20of%20these%20features%3A%20stucco%20finishes%2C%20a%20metal%20roof%2C%20tempered%20windows%2C%20no%20roof%20vents%20or%20eaves%20on%20its%20sides.%20But%20there's%20an%20even%20smaller%20adjustment%20that%20may%20have%20helped%20keep%20the%20flames%20away%3A%20a%20buffer%20around%20the%20house%20devoid%20of%20vegetation.%20Jursnick%20recalls%20a%20conversation%20with%20another%20architect%20who%20likened%20nearby%20plants%20and%20bushes%20to%20the%20tinder%20you'd%20use%20to%20light%20a%20campfire.%20Removing%20those%20is%20an%20example%20of%20a%20little%20thing%20even%20weekend-warrior%20home-improvement%20types%20can%20do%20to%20better%20protect%20their%20homes.%20Another%20is%20replacing%20old%20vents%20with%20newer%20models%20designed%20to%20deny%20entry%20to%20embers.%20Costlier%20measures%20include%20swapping%20in%20a%20metal%20fence%20for%20the%20wooden%20version%20or%20opting%20for%20a%20new%20metal%20roof.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EDecades-old%20homes%2C%20like%20many%20in%20the%20Pacific%20Palisades%20and%20Altadena%2C%20are%20much%20more%20susceptible%20to%20fires%20than%20newer%20builds.%20But%20retrofitting%20them%20to%20meet%20modern%20codes%20is%20more%20expensive%20than%20adding%20fire-resistant%20features%20to%20new%20construction%20from%20the%20get-go.%20Research%20from%20the%20environmental%20economists%20Patrick%20Baylis%20and%20Judson%20Boomhower%20suggests%20that%20California%20homes%20built%20after%20the%20state%20tightened%20its%20building%20codes%20in%202008%20are%20about%2040%25%20less%20likely%20to%20be%20destroyed%20in%20a%20fire%20than%20a%201990%20home%20exposed%20to%20an%20identical%20blaze.%20Another%20study%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcalifornia-camp-fire-death-toll-most-destructive-in-history-2018-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2018%20Camp%20Fire%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20destroyed%20most%20of%20the%20town%20of%20Paradise%20in%20northern%20California%2C%20found%20that%20only%2011.5%25%20of%20single-family%20homes%20built%20within%20city%20limits%20before%201997%20survived%2C%20compared%20with%20a%2038.5%25%20survival%20rate%20for%20those%20built%20that%20year%20or%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoomhower%20walked%20away%20from%20his%20study%20convinced%20that%20more%20local%20governments%20should%20mandate%20fire-resistant%20building%20codes%20rather%20than%20wait%20for%20builders%20and%20homeowners%20to%20wise%20up%20to%20their%20benefits.%20Normally%2C%20an%20economist%20like%20him%20might%20be%20skeptical%20of%20government%20rules%20for%20something%20that%20is%20so%20obviously%20a%20good%20investment%20%E2%80%94%20buyers%20of%20new%20homes%20should%20be%20motivated%20to%20protect%20what%20is%20likely%20their%20biggest%20asset%2C%20codes%20be%20damned.%20But%20Boomhower's%20study%20found%20limited%20adoption%20of%20these%20best%20practices%20in%20areas%20that%20didn't%20require%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHomebuilders%20and%20home%20buyers%20are%20just%20not%20always%20aware%20of%20the%20risks%20and%20aware%20of%20the%20low-hanging-fruit%20options%20for%20mitigation%2C%26quot%3B%20Boomhower%20tells%20me.%20The%20data%20also%20suggests%20there%20are%20spillover%20effects%20that%20could%20protect%20non-improved%20homes%3A%20Investments%20made%20by%20just%20one%20homeowner%20can%20help%20stunt%20the%20spread%20of%20a%20blaze%2C%20making%20it%20less%20likely%20that%20their%20neighbors'%20homes%20burn%20down.%20And%20insurers%20may%20be%20more%20willing%20to%20extend%20policies%20to%20homeowners%20in%20areas%20where%20they%20know%20many%20builds%20meet%20these%20criteria.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20far%20from%20just%20a%20California%20issue.%20A%20handful%20of%20states%2C%20including%20Montana%2C%20Nevada%2C%20and%20Pennsylvania%2C%20and%20200%20local%20jurisdictions%20have%20adopted%20the%20International%20Code%20Council's%20standards%20for%20building%20fire-resistant%20homes%20in%20WUIs.%20Austin%2C%20for%20example%2C%20adopted%20the%20code%20in%202015%20and%20is%20considering%20an%20update%20that%20would%20expand%20the%20WUI's%20borders%20in%20hopes%20of%20protecting%20more%20homes.%20Homeowners%20that%20go%20beyond%20even%20the%20strictest%20codes%2C%20either%20during%20the%20initial%20construction%20or%20as%20part%20of%20a%20retrofit%2C%20may%20score%20discounts%20from%20insurers%20or%20state-level%20tax%20breaks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20even%20with%20city-level%20and%20homeowner-level%20interventions%2C%20Eliason%20tells%20me%2C%20%26quot%3Bthere's%20no%20guarantee%20of%20protection.%26quot%3B%20The%20logical%20thing%2C%20he%20says%2C%20would%20be%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-burned-los-angeles-neighborhoods-can-do-survive-next-fires-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebuild%20more%20densely%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20areas%20far%20from%20the%20WUI%20to%20limit%20the%20number%20of%20homes%20at%20risk%20in%20the%20first%20place.%20In%20the%20absence%20of%20that%20kind%20of%20fix%20%E2%80%94%20which%20would%20involve%20sweeping%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyimbys-winning-lower-house-prices-rents-build-more-homes-neighborhoods-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echanges%20to%20the%20zoning%20laws%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20say%20what%20you%20can%20build%20and%20where%20%E2%80%94%20better%20materials%20and%20design%20can%20make%20a%20difference.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJursnick%2C%20the%20Denver-area%20architect%2C%20has%20been%20thinking%20about%20this%20stuff%20a%20lot%20recently.%20He's%20working%20on%20plans%20for%20an%20apartment%20building%20in%20an%20area%20just%20outside%20Boulder%20that%20was%20burned%20in%202021%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsurviving-marshall-fire-colorado-what-los-angeles-should-expect-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMarshall%20Fire%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20destroyed%20more%20than%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboulder-colorado-wildfire-vacant-lots-sold-marshall-fire-rebuild-housing-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E1%2C000%20homes%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Much%20of%20the%20community%20input%2C%20he%20says%2C%20has%20revolved%20around%20how%20to%20prevent%20that%20kind%20of%20tragedy%20from%20happening%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20we're%20going%20to%20keep%20building%20more%20homes%20in%20those%20areas%2C%26quot%3B%20Jursnick%20tells%20me%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20we%20need%20to%20be%20more%20thoughtful%20of%20how%20we%20build%2C%20and%20adapt%20our%20building%20strategies%20in%20those%20areas%20to%20acknowledge%20that%20risk.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fjames-rodriguez%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EJames%20Rodriguez%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20reporter%20on%20Business%20Insider's%20Discourse%20team.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flos-angeles-wildfires-fireproof-my-home-roofs-siding-building-code-2025-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1738141622000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F678fe959ae09223df2bad223%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flos-angeles-wildfires-fireproof-my-home-roofs-siding-building-code-2025-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20third%20of%20American%20homes%2C%20or%20about%2048%20million%20properties%2C%20are%20at%20risk%20of%20wildfires.%20Here's%20how%20to%20protect%20yours.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jrodriguez%40insider.com%20(James%20Rodriguez)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A22%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flos-angeles-wildfires-fireproof-my-home-roofs-siding-building-code-2025-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20'friendship%20app'%20connected%20me%20with%20five%20strangers.%20We%20actually%20hit%20it%20off.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Lonely%20person%20in%20front%20of%20a%20phone%20surrounded%20by%20friendship%20apps%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6799598f196626c409858ffb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3B%20Alyssa%20Powell%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20one%20of%20the%20coldest%20nights%20in%20New%20York%20this%20year%2C%20I%20bundled%20up%20and%20went%20to%20a%20trendy%20tourist%20trap%20to%20meet%20up%20with%20five%20people%20who%20also%20felt%20that%20the%20pull%20to%20make%20new%20friends%20was%20stronger%20than%20the%20windchill.%20I%20didn't%20know%20anything%20about%20my%20matches%20aside%20from%20a%20text%20I'd%20received%20that%20told%20me%20that%20two%20of%20them%20also%20like%20reading%2C%20that%20several%20enjoyed%20the%20same%20irreverent%20TV%20shows%20I%20do%2C%20like%20%26quot%3BArrested%20Development%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BBroad%20City%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20one%20had%20bungee%20jumped%20in%20New%20Zealand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20were%20meeting%20as%20a%20group%20curated%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstartup-shifting-social-to-real-life-funding-raise-app-launch-2024-2%23%3A~%3Atext%3D222%252C%2520which%2520launched%2520in%2520Los%2Ca%2520series%2520of%2520backyard%2520dinners.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ethe%20app%20222%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20asks%20users%20to%20fill%20out%20questionnaires%20with%20info%20like%20their%20birth%20order%20among%20their%20siblings%2C%20the%20economic%20class%20they%20grew%20up%20in%2C%20and%20how%20spontaneous%20they%20are.%20I%20was%20delighted%20to%20see%20I%20was%20paired%20with%20other%20people%20in%20their%20late%2020s%20and%20early%2030s%2C%20so%20I%20wouldn't%20have%20to%20be%20the%20aging%20millennial%20at%20the%20Gen%20Z%20table.%20(There%20was%20a%20collective%20sigh%20of%20relief%20on%20this%20point.)%20Despite%20the%20freezing%20cold%2C%20everyone%20showed%20up%20%E2%80%94%20no%20doubt%20given%20extra%20motivation%20by%20the%20app's%20strict%20no-show%20policy%20that%20not%20only%20involves%20added%20fees%20but%20kicks%20out%20people%20who%20don't%20cancel%20with%20notice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20app%2C%20acting%20as%20a%20sort%20of%20virtual%20host%2C%20gave%20us%20prompts%20to%20get%20the%20conversation%20going%2C%20such%20as%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20could%20pick%20another%20name%20for%20yourself%2C%20what%20would%20it%20be%3F%26quot%3B.%20I%20didn't%20find%20them%20particularly%20enlightening.%20We%20read%20through%20some%20but%20decided%20we%20didn't%20need%20generic%20prompts%20to%20chat.%20The%20people%20who%20had%20bought%20into%20this%20experience%20(by%20paying%20a%20small%20fee%20to%20222%20and%20by%20opening%20themselves%20up%20to%20strangers)%20were%20friendly%20and%20eager%20to%20meet%20someone%20new.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFounded%20in%202021%2C%20222%20is%20one%20of%20several%20apps%20that%20launched%20in%20recent%20years%20with%20the%20aim%20of%20fighting%20loneliness%20and%20finding%20people%20real%2C%20in-the-flesh%20friends.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-make-friends-as-adult-bumble-bff-strategy-tips-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EBumble%20has%20for%20years%20had%20a%20friendship%20setting%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20swiping.%20There's%20also%20Clockout%2C%20Timeleft%2C%20and%20Pie.%20Timeleft%20says%20it%20has%20brought%20more%20than%20400%2C000%20people%20together%20in%20more%20than%20170%20cities.%20In%202023%2C%20Bumble%20estimated%20that%20about%2015%25%20of%20its%20monthly%20active%20users%20were%20using%20the%20friends%20setting.%20While%20social%20media%20algorithms%20are%20often%20blamed%20for%20entrapping%20people%20and%20isolating%20them%20as%20they%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcure-for-doomscrolling-shaming-your-friends-screentime-app-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Espend%20more%20of%20their%20time%20on%20screens%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20with%20friends%2C%20apps%20like%20222%20say%20their%20algorithms%20can%20pair%20us%20up%20with%20our%20new%20besties%20or%20potential%20romantic%20partners%2C%20sussing%20out%20similarities%20and%20determining%20compatibility.%20A%20cottage%20industry%20of%20apps%20is%20raising%20millions%20of%20dollars%20on%20the%20idea%20that%20IRL%20is%20the%20next%20big%20thing%20online.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20apps%20feel%20like%20the%20next%20iteration%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbumble-match-dating-apps-earnings-swipe-fatigue-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eonline%20dating%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20normalized%20the%20virtual%20meet-cute.%20But%20they're%20having%20a%20moment%20as%20more%20young%20people%20feel%20burned%20out%20by%20the%20churn%20of%20commodified%20romance.%20Finding%20friendship%20is%20lower%20stakes%20than%20finding%20true%20love%2C%20but%20that's%20also%20a%20part%20of%20the%20barrier%20to%20it.%20There%20are%20fewer%20norms%20for%20pursuing%20a%20potential%20friend%3A%20How%20soon%20after%20meeting%20do%20I%20text%20them%3F%20How%20do%20I%20know%20if%20they're%20interested%20as%20well%3F%20Am%20I%20being%20too%20needy%3F%20Does%20this%20person%20think%20I'm%20a%20total%20freak%3F%20The%20anxiety%20spiral%20can%20keep%20any%20of%20us%20from%20texting%20someone%20to%20hang%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20point%20of%20222%20is%20to%20get%20past%20that.%20%26quot%3BIf%20we%20can%20use%20technology%20to%20be%20an%20invisible%20facilitator%20to%20just%20nudge%20people%20gently%20in%20the%20direction%20of%20spending%20more%20time%20with%20each%20other%2C%20then%20I%20think%20we've%20truly%20created%20more%20connection%20in%20the%20world%2C%26quot%3B%20Keyan%20Kazemian%2C%20the%2025-year-old%20cofounder%20and%20CEO%20of%20222%2C%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BWe've%20created%20a%20chance%20encounter%20and%20potentially%20a%20relationship%20that%20didn't%20exist%20before.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20pandemic%20there%20was%20a%20rise%20in%20the%20celebration%20of%20canceling%20plans%2C%20as%20showcased%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.stylist.co.uk%2Frelationships%2Fcancelling-plans%2F541657%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eviral%20social%20media%20posts%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20several%20articles%20unpacking%20the%20psychology%20behind%20the%20act.%20It%20felt%20so%20good%2C%20many%20people%20said%2C%20to%20bail%20and%20binge%20Netflix%20instead%20of%20shuttling%20around%20to%20after-work%20catch-up%20cocktails%20with%20friends.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20just%20not%20feeling%20it%26quot%3B%20became%20a%20justification%20for%20ditching%20someone%20over%20text%20on%20short%20notice%20and%20choosing%20to%20rot%20on%20the%20couch%20instead.%20Leaving%20friends%20on%20read%20for%20days%20became%20the%20norm.%20People%20prioritized%20individualism%20and%20the%20idea%20of%20self-care%20over%20community%20and%20friendships.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20backlash%20from%20the%20self-involved%20era%20is%20in%20full%20swing.%20Turns%20out%2C%20people%20want%20friends.%20They%20want%20to%20practice%20the%20lost%20art%20of%20hanging%20out%2C%20central%20to%20'90s%20sitcoms%20like%20%26quot%3BFriends%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BSeinfeld.%26quot%3B%20But%20as%20we've%20increasingly%20lost%20our%20connection%20to%20%26quot%3Bthird%20places%2C%26quot%3B%20like%20religious%20centers%2C%20local%20coffee%20shops%2C%20and%20community%20centers%2C%20and%20pivoted%20toward%20hybrid%20or%20remote%20work%2C%20finding%20our%20people%20has%20become%20so%20much%20harder.%20Former%20US%20surgeon%20general%2C%20Dr.%20Vivek%20Murthy%20called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-surgeon-general-compares-loneliness-epidemic-to-smoking-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eloneliness%20an%20epidemic%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202023%2C%20highlighting%20the%20serious%20physical%20health%20risks%20and%20financial%20costs%20of%20isolation.%20In%20a%202024%20poll%20conducted%20by%20Morning%20Consult%20for%20the%20American%20Psychiatric%20Association%2C%2030%25%20of%20adults%20said%20they%20felt%20lonely%20once%20a%20week%2C%20and%2010%25%20said%20they%20felt%20lonely%20daily.%20Among%2018-%20to%2034-year-olds%2C%2030%25%20said%20they%20felt%20lonely%20each%20day%20or%20several%20times%20a%20week.%20The%20definition%20of%20loneliness%20for%20the%20poll%20wasn't%20just%20having%20a%20slow%20week%20or%20lacking%20a%20romantic%20partner%20but%20the%20much%20darker%20dread%20of%20%26quot%3Bfeeling%20like%20you%20do%20not%20have%20meaningful%20or%20close%20relationships%20or%20a%20sense%20of%20belonging.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20look%20at%20the%20increasing%20ways%20people%20are%20trying%20to%20study%20and%20understand%20the%20science%20of%20making%20friends%2C%20the%20idea%20of%20using%20algorithms%20doesn't%20seem%20so%20far-fetched.%20A%202018%20study%20from%20Jeffrey%20Hall%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20communication%20studies%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Kansas%2C%20found%20that%20people%20had%20to%20spend%20about%2050%20hours%20together%20to%20become%20casual%20friends%20and%2090%20hours%20to%20reach%20general%20%26quot%3Bfriend%26quot%3B%20status.%20Another%20study%20he%20conducted%20in%202023%20suggested%20that%20reaching%20out%20to%20friends%20for%20even%20quick%20quality%20interactions%20daily%20could%20help%20lower%20stress%20and%20increase%20happiness.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20apps%20like%20222%20and%20Timeleft%2C%20the%20algorithms%20may%20matter%20less%20than%20the%20buy-in%3A%20The%20apps%20gather%20people%20who%20want%20to%20make%20new%20friends%20and%20then%20push%20them%20to%20follow%20up%2C%20avoiding%20some%20of%20the%20awkwardness%20of%20pursuing%20something%20unreciprocated.%20%26quot%3BWhether%20or%20not%20the%20specific%20magic%20sauce%20of%20the%20matching%20is%20necessary%20is%20an%20open%20question.%20It%20might%20work%2C%20it%20might%20not%20work%2C%20it%20may%20not%20matter%2C%26quot%3B%20Hall%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20really%20matters%20is%20people%20are%20caring%20enough%20to%20sign%20up%20and%20show%20up%2C%20and%20showing%20up%20is%20what%20we%20do%20for%20our%20friends.%26quot%3B%20I%20tried%20another%20matched%20dinner%20on%20Timeleft%2C%20which%20tries%20to%20match%20compatible%20people%20for%20Wednesday-night%20dinners%20around%20the%20US%2C%20but%20half%20of%20our%20group%20ditched%2C%20which%20made%20it%20harder%20to%20have%20the%20full%20group%20experience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpitch-deck-irl-social-startup-pie-raises-andy-dunn-bonobos-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EPie%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20brings%20people%20together%20around%20shared%20interests%20%E2%80%94%20like%20book%20clubs%2C%20dinner%20clubs%2C%20and%20dancing%20%E2%80%94%20in%20Chicago%2C%20Austin%2C%20and%20San%20Francisco.%20The%20company%20pays%20local%20creators%20to%20host%20events%2C%20leveraging%20the%20concept%20of%20the%20gig%20economy%20and%20local%20social%20groups%20as%20an%20engine%20for%20new%20connections.%20Andy%20Dunn%2C%20who%20founded%20Pie%20after%20his%20run%20as%20the%20cofounder%20and%20CEO%20of%20the%20menswear%20brand%20Bonobos%2C%20says%20people%20have%20to%20keep%20seeing%20each%20other%20to%20form%20those%20strong%20ties.%20For%20now%2C%20Pie%20brings%20people%20together%20for%20recurring%20events%2C%20but%20it's%20working%20on%20ways%20to%20better%20pair%20up%20people%20at%20those%20events%20who%20are%20likely%20to%20get%20along.%20Dunn%20says%20he%20thinks%20the%20answer%20to%20ending%20loneliness%20isn't%20technology%20itself%20but%20rather%20people%20who%20decide%20to%20show%20up%20and%20put%20themselves%20out%20there.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20think%20the%20algorithm%20can%20do%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20%3Cem%3Ewe%3C%2Fem%3E%20can%20do%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20idea%20is%20catching%20on.%20Pie%20raised%20%2411.5%20million%20in%20a%20Series%20A%20round%20last%20year%2C%20and%20222%20raised%20%243.6%20million%20so%20far.%20%26quot%3BWhile%20technology%20has%20offered%20us%20so%20much%2C%20including%20a%20new%20dimension%20of%20connectivity%20via%20social%20networks%2C%20it%20has%20had%20many%20unintended%20consequences%20that%20have%20led%20in%20part%20to%2C%20ironically%2C%20less%20connectivity%20in%20real%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20Kirsten%20Green%2C%20the%20founder%20and%20managing%20partner%20of%20Forerunner%20Ventures%20who%20invested%20in%20Pie%2C%20tells%20me%20in%20an%20email.%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20entering%20what%20we%20see%20as%20the%20next%20phase%20of%20digital%20adoption%20where%20we%20better%20learn%20to%20live%20with%20this%20%E2%80%94%20not%20by%20being%20consumed%20by%20it%2C%20but%20by%20thriving%20because%20of%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20thinking%20about%20the%20gaggle%20of%20people%20I've%20collected%20as%20my%20closest%20friends%20over%20the%20past%2020%20years.%20Two%20I%20met%20through%20Craigslist%20and%20Facebook%20Marketplace%20as%20random%20roommates%20who%20also%20needed%20someone%20to%20split%20the%20rent%20with.%20Another%20was%20my%20last-minute%20prom%20date%2C%20and%20the%20fourth%20I%20picked%20out%20of%20my%20300%20or%20so%20seventh-grade%20peers%20because%20she%20wore%20a%20Panic!%20At%20The%20Disco%20T-shirt.%20Each%20was%20brought%20into%20my%20life%20by%20repeated%20proximity%20%E2%80%94%20we%20shared%20classrooms%20or%20kitchens%20and%20living%20rooms%20and%20experiences%20for%20so%20long%20that%20we%20eventually%20became%20inseparable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20recently%20asked%20one%20of%20them%3A%20Do%20you%20think%20we're%20best%20friends%20because%20we%20can%20see%20the%20subtleties%20of%20the%20world%20in%20the%20same%20way%2C%20or%20do%20we%20see%20the%20world%20the%20same%20way%20because%20we've%20been%20hanging%20out%20since%202007%3F%20How%20much%20of%20our%20compatibility%20is%20innate%2C%20and%20how%20much%20have%20we%20built%20into%20each%20other%20by%20spending%20thousands%20upon%20thousands%20of%20hours%20together%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHall%20says%20friendships%20are%20likely%20forged%20at%20both%20ends.%20You%20discover%20that%20you%20have%20a%20similar%20worldview%20or%20sense%20of%20humor%20in%20certain%20situations.%20Over%20time%2C%20your%20friends%20also%20shape%20you%3A%20They%20can%20influence%20your%20values%2C%20your%20exercise%20routine%2C%20your%20eating%20and%20drinking%20habits.%20Similarity%20alone%20is%20not%20enough.%20We%20could%20read%20the%20same%20book%20but%20have%20completely%20different%20interpretations.%20We%20might%20both%20be%20dog%20people%2C%20but%20that%20doesn't%20mean%20I'll%20like%20you%20and%20your%20dog.%20But%20my%20random%20roommates%20and%20I%2C%20who%20look%20different%20on%20paper%20and%20were%20brought%20together%20over%20nothing%20more%20than%20similar%20budgets%20in%20the%20same%20city%2C%20can%20look%20at%20a%20social%20situation%20and%20walk%20away%20with%20the%20same%20vibes%20and%20opinions.%20Would%20an%20algorithm%20match%20me%20with%20these%20people%20for%20dinner%3F%20If%20it%20did%2C%20would%20I%20even%20recognize%20their%20potential%20to%20be%20the%20people%20who'll%20stand%20by%20me%20during%20my%20most%20important%20life%20events%3F%20There's%20no%20way%20to%20know.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20day%20or%20so%20after%20my%20222%20dinner%2C%20the%20app%20asked%20me%20to%20rate%20my%20dinner%20companions%20and%20provide%20more%20info%20on%20why%20I%20did%20or%20didn't%20like%20someone.%20It%20said%20that%20would%20help%20boost%20my%20chance%20of%20getting%20better%20matches%20going%20forward.%20After%20filling%20out%20the%20questionnaire%2C%20I%20found%20that%20someone%20I%20had%20positively%20reviewed%20said%20the%20same%20about%20me%2C%20and%20the%20app%20nudged%20us%20to%20hang%20out%20again%20%E2%80%94%20taking%20the%20awkwardness%20of%20pursuing%20a%20new%20pal%20out%20of%20my%20hands.%20It%20may%20matter%20less%20what%20the%20algorithm%20sees%20in%20the%20two%20of%20us%20and%20more%20that%20we're%20open%20to%20keep%20trying%20to%20find%20our%20people%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fphones-loneliness-friendship-apps-dating-fatigue-meetups-algorithms-2025-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1738141502000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F679959e67bb3f854015aed28%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fphones-loneliness-friendship-apps-dating-fatigue-meetups-algorithms-2025-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Our%20phones%20have%20made%20us%20lonelier.%20These%20apps%20promise%20to%20find%20us%20a%2