20than%206%2C000%20employees.%20He%20described%20the%20layoffs%20as%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-laying-off-twitter-was-painful-bbc-spaces-interview-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Epainful%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bone%20of%20the%20hardest%20things%26quot%3B%20he'd%20had%20to%20do%20as%20Twitter's%20boss.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20government%20has%20also%20taken%20on%20a%20lot%20of%20debt%20in%20recent%20years.%20While%20no%20one%20expects%20a%20US%20default%20anytime%20soon%2C%20the%20national%20debt%20soared%20from%20about%20%243.4%20trillion%20in%201980%20to%20more%20than%20%2435%20trillion%20last%20year.%20Roughly%20%2410%20trillion%20in%20debt%20piled%20up%20from%202017%20to%202024%2C%20according%20to%20Treasury%20Department%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffiscaldata.treasury.gov%2Famericas-finance-guide%2Fnational-debt%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Edata%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERising%20rates%20have%20increased%20the%20cost%20of%20paying%20interest%20on%20this%20massive%20debt%20load.%20In%202023%2C%20these%20annual%20payments%20topped%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fbonds%2Fus-debt-interest-payments-federal-deficit-treasury-bonds-fed-hikes-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%241%20trillion%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20stoking%20concern%20among%20some%20economists%20about%20government%20spending.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20partly%20what's%20driving%20the%20Trump%20administration%20to%20try%20to%20make%20the%20US%20government%20more%20efficient.%20Trump%20has%20also%20pledged%20to%20pursue%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-pay-in-taxes-trump-tax-bill-expiring-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Etax%20cuts%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20putting%20even%20more%20pressure%20on%20his%20administration%20to%20find%20other%20ways%20of%20con